# Windows

Install xcsh on Windows using PowerShell.

## Quick Install

Download and extract the latest release:

=== "PowerShell (amd64)"

    ```powershell
    # Download latest release
    $version = "{{ version or 'X.Y.Z' }}"
    $url = "https://github.com/robinmordasiewicz/xcsh/releases/download/v$version/xcsh_${version}_windows_amd64.zip"
    Invoke-WebRequest -Uri $url -OutFile xcsh.zip

    # Extract to installation directory
    $installDir = "$env:LOCALAPPDATA\Programs\xcsh"
    New-Item -ItemType Directory -Force -Path $installDir | Out-Null
    Expand-Archive -Path xcsh.zip -DestinationPath $installDir -Force

    # Add to PATH for current session
    $env:PATH = "$installDir;$env:PATH"

    # Verify installation
    xcsh version
    ```

